  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Harinagar Sugar Mills Ltd. (Biscuit Division) & Anr. versus State of Maharashtra & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_7_427_462','2025INSC801'); ><font size='4'> <strong>HARINAGAR SUGAR MILLS LTD. (BISCUIT DIVISION) & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF MAHARASHTRA & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 7 S.C.R. 427</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 801</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002822025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : SANJAY KAROL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, PRASHANT KUMAR MISHRA</strong><br> Issue for Consideration (i) Whether letter dated 25.09.2019 sent by the Deputy Secretary of State Government can be construed to be an order - Connectedly, whether the appellants would be entitled to the relief of deemed closure, as on 27.10.2019 by virtue of the in s. 25-O(3) of the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947; (ii) What would be the meaning of the phrase &lsquo;appropriate Government&rsquo; and whether in the facts of this case, it was the appropriate Government acting in the matter of the closure - if not what is the effect in law, thereof.<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 04-06-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 7372/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_7_427_462','2025INSC801','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></